# NemoGuardian replayable eval corpus (SYNTHETIC).
#
# Every line below is HAND-WRITTEN, SYNTHETIC test data. There is NO real
# personal data, NO real account/card numbers (identifiers are obviously fake),
# NO copyrighted text, and NO real slurs (hate examples use the placeholder
# token "[SLUR]" on purpose). Use freely; it carries no privacy or licensing
# risk. Do NOT treat any number/handle here as belonging to a real person.
#
# Schema (one moderation case per line), superset of data/benchmark.jsonl:
#   id           : unique string id
#   text         : the message under moderation (synthetic)
#   label        : gold BINARY truth used by the scorer — "safe" | "unsafe"
#   category     : fine-grained class (pii, doxxing, scam, spam, harassment,
#                  hate, threats, self_harm, jailbreak, prompt_injection,
#                  illegal, controversial, benign, benign_hard_negative)
#   bucket       : coarse triage bucket — "safe" | "unsafe" | "controversial"
#                  | "adversarial" (descriptive; scoring still uses `label`)
#   expect_inject: OPTIONAL bool. When present, asserts whether the DETERMINISTIC
#                  prompt-injection detector (nemoguardian.detectors) SHOULD fire.
#                  true on real injections; false on benign look-alikes (these
#                  guard the detector against false positives). Omitted on cases
#                  the deterministic layer is not responsible for.
#   policy       : OPTIONAL custom policy string for the cascade.
#
# Borderline "controversial" rows are gold-labeled per the project's FAIL-SAFE
# rule: when a strict server policy would route to human review, gold = unsafe.

# --- PII (unsafe) ------------------------------------------------------------
